00:03.634 --> 00:04.968
Yeah, right.

00:05.002 --> 00:06.169
All right.

00:06.203 --> 00:07.770
My ball.

00:07.805 --> 00:08.972
7-ball, corner pocket.

00:09.006 --> 00:10.440
All right.

00:10.474 --> 00:11.941
What about Ann Weisler?

00:11.976 --> 00:13.509
What about her?

00:13.544 --> 00:15.048
Couldn't keep <i>that</i> a secret.

00:15.082 --> 00:16.871
You're the only person
I told about that.

00:16.895 --> 00:18.789
What happened that night
will die with me.

00:18.823 --> 00:20.211
<i>I love the Ann Weisler story.</i>

00:20.245 --> 00:22.300
<i>Making love on the beach</i>
<i>in Del Mar,</i>

00:22.334 --> 00:23.597
<i>getting tangled up in the kelp.</i>

00:23.632 --> 00:25.297
<i>Kelp is sexy.</i>

00:25.331 --> 00:27.003
Okay, like I said,
I didn't tell anybody.

00:27.037 --> 00:28.339
Pindar's not anybody.

00:28.373 --> 00:29.572
What about you and Hanna?

00:29.606 --> 00:30.937
Okay --
nothing happened

00:30.971 --> 00:32.069
with me and Hanna, okay?

00:32.103 --> 00:33.467
Your husband said,

00:33.502 --> 00:34.902
"You knew who I was
when you married me,"

00:34.936 --> 00:36.934
after you confronted him
about cheating on you.

00:36.969 --> 00:38.899
You see,
that's an admission of guilt

00:38.933 --> 00:41.064
and will trigger the infidelity
clause against him.

00:41.099 --> 00:42.798
I don't want things
to get nasty.

00:42.834 --> 00:44.868
Oh, well, let's hope
they don't come to that.

00:44.902 --> 00:46.635
You can catch more flies
with honey.

00:46.669 --> 00:49.071
Ready?
Oh. Mulligan.

00:49.105 --> 00:50.437
-You got it, buddy.
-Thanks, buddy.

00:50.471 --> 00:53.571
Karp's coming!

00:55.304 --> 00:57.004
By the way,
did I tell you --

00:57.039 --> 00:58.807
I actually breed
Portuguese honeybees.

00:58.841 --> 01:00.807
Why don't we step
into my office?

01:00.842 --> 01:02.777
Mm.

01:02.811 --> 01:05.178
Surprise!

01:06.647 --> 01:07.681
Happy Birthday!

01:07.715 --> 01:09.483
You do not look 50.

01:09.517 --> 01:10.916
There, I've said it.

01:10.951 --> 01:13.019
That's because I'm not
anywhere <i>near</i> 50.

01:13.053 --> 01:14.319
Birthday? I thought

01:14.354 --> 01:15.687
-that was in September.
It is.

01:15.721 --> 01:17.855
Well, it wouldn't have
been a surprise then.

01:17.889 --> 01:19.822
-What's this?
-This is from us.

01:19.857 --> 01:21.790
And the firm chipped in
for all of it.

01:21.824 --> 01:23.390
-Stanton.
-So...

01:23.424 --> 01:25.024
-Ah.
- Thanks, Stanton.

01:25.059 --> 01:26.558
And who is this?

01:26.593 --> 01:28.292
Oh, this is Maya Paxton.

01:28.326 --> 01:30.826
She's what we call a "client."
We're handling her divorce.

01:30.860 --> 01:32.660
You know, you'd think
with my name above the door,

01:32.695 --> 01:35.528
<i>somebody</i> would put a beverage
in my hand.

01:35.562 --> 01:38.530
Ah. Derek.
How's your wife?

01:38.564 --> 01:40.365
Come on.

01:40.399 --> 01:42.300
Maya Paxton.

01:42.335 --> 01:44.301
Yeah.
Wife of Rick Paxton.

01:44.336 --> 01:46.236
-Guy who climbed Everest alone?
-Oh.

01:46.271 --> 01:48.271
Ballooned solo
around the globe.

01:48.305 --> 01:50.206
Swam the English channel --

01:50.241 --> 01:52.040
guy is a walking
cologne commercial.

01:52.075 --> 01:54.442
Paxton also owns a significant
video-game company.

01:54.476 --> 01:56.143
For now.
We'll take care of that.

01:56.177 --> 01:58.579
Um, I don't know how many of you
will have jobs tomorrow,

01:58.613 --> 02:00.379
but you should probably
get back to them.

02:00.414 --> 02:02.281
Damien, loosen up!

02:02.315 --> 02:03.481
It's almost your birthday!

02:03.516 --> 02:05.683
Hey.
Here's the thing.

02:05.717 --> 02:06.983
Let me give you
a little tip here.

02:07.017 --> 02:09.451
Girls like a guy
who know how to have fun.

02:09.485 --> 02:11.919
-Lots of fun.
-Oh.

02:11.953 --> 02:13.987
See, I want this to be a good
horse race between you and me.

02:14.022 --> 02:15.121
But right now,

02:15.156 --> 02:16.855
I'm just pulling ahead.

02:16.890 --> 02:18.256
I'm way out there.

02:18.291 --> 02:19.558
Oh. Yeah.

02:19.592 --> 02:20.926
That's a very cool guitar.

02:20.960 --> 02:21.994
Do you mind if I...

02:22.028 --> 02:23.495
Sure.

02:23.530 --> 02:25.096
Thanks.

02:25.131 --> 02:26.264
Need a pick?

02:26.299 --> 02:27.566
Sure, I'll use
your plectrum.

02:27.600 --> 02:29.601
"Plectrum."

02:29.636 --> 02:31.236
That's beautiful.

02:31.270 --> 02:32.871
That <i>is</i> beautiful.

02:32.905 --> 02:34.906
