03:57.279 --> 03:59.379
Let me ask you --

03:59.414 --> 04:01.715
if you were a chick,
would you go for me or Karp?

04:01.749 --> 04:03.350
-Karp.
-What?

04:03.384 --> 04:05.952
What? He's got the
Porsche, the Wilshire condo,

04:05.986 --> 04:07.119
the Soho house membership.

04:07.154 --> 04:08.587
Okay,
you are one vapid chick.

04:08.621 --> 04:10.289
You know what?
I don't even want to date you.

04:10.323 --> 04:11.957
Well, it's a moot point,
'cause I'd be boning Karp.

04:11.991 --> 04:13.291
I want to see
other people.

04:13.325 --> 04:14.492
Go ahead.

04:14.526 --> 04:16.060
Oh!

04:16.095 --> 04:17.128
Is that...

04:17.161 --> 04:18.529
Everybody's all-American!

04:18.563 --> 04:20.531
Danny Dubois!

04:20.565 --> 04:22.634
Double D! Yeah!

04:22.668 --> 04:24.203
How great is this place,

04:24.237 --> 04:26.037
after 10 years
you can still cruise it

04:26.072 --> 04:27.638
and know something's
happening here?

04:27.673 --> 04:29.273
Yeah, that <i>is</i> great.
We should move.

04:29.308 --> 04:30.975
Well, Double D heard that.

04:32.778 --> 04:34.179
You did the thing
with the face!

04:34.213 --> 04:35.680
Let's move in together!

04:35.714 --> 04:37.282
We should!
That wouldn't be awkward at all!

04:37.316 --> 04:38.750
Last we heard,

04:38.784 --> 04:41.019
you were some hedge-fund guy
in Connecticut.

04:41.054 --> 04:42.387
Yeah. Just out here
visiting family.

04:42.422 --> 04:44.089
Sure you don't want a drink?

04:44.123 --> 04:46.224
No, thanks.
I do need a lawyer, though.

04:46.259 --> 04:48.160
Last week, I got caught up
in a little brawl.

04:48.194 --> 04:50.295
-Like a brouhaha?
- I don't know.

04:50.330 --> 04:51.731
I was at a strip club,

04:51.765 --> 04:52.999
and there were beer, fists,
and teeth flying.

04:53.033 --> 04:54.267
-Ah, a donnybrook.
-Ah.

04:54.301 --> 04:55.735
Oh. Sweet.

04:55.769 --> 04:57.536
So I thought I'd throw
a little business your way,

04:57.570 --> 04:59.638
and since Bash here
is tapping the D.A...

04:59.672 --> 05:01.540
We broke up.

05:01.574 --> 05:03.075
That sucks.

05:03.109 --> 05:04.977
Yeah, also, we're
with Infeld/Daniels now.

05:05.011 --> 05:06.612
We don't really do donnybrooks.

05:06.646 --> 05:08.680
So give us a call when you start
embezzling pension funds.

05:08.714 --> 05:10.148
Nad!

05:10.182 --> 05:11.983
Still a wise-ass!

05:12.017 --> 05:14.720
Don't call me "Nad."

05:17.122 --> 05:19.257
Danny's a tool.

05:19.292 --> 05:21.526
He was a tool back then,
he's a tool now.

05:21.561 --> 05:24.262
Is this about
the shower thing?

05:24.297 --> 05:25.864
Oh, come on.

05:25.898 --> 05:27.466
That was 15 years ago!

05:27.500 --> 05:28.700
Yeah.

05:28.735 --> 05:30.903
Fine. You know what?
We'll do it.

05:30.937 --> 05:33.739
Any excuse for you
to see your ex.

05:37.677 --> 05:39.911
Danny was at home
when his buddy Mike Cromwell

05:39.945 --> 05:41.412
called from the club.

05:41.447 --> 05:42.747
Some guys were messing
with Mike and he needed backup,

05:42.782 --> 05:43.849
so he called Danny.

05:43.883 --> 05:45.283
So why call the cops?

05:45.318 --> 05:46.818
Danny ends up
getting his ass kicked

05:46.853 --> 05:48.120
while Mike hid behind the bar.

05:48.154 --> 05:49.788
Guess who gets charged
with the assault.

05:49.822 --> 05:51.557
-Your client.
-Exactly.

05:51.591 --> 05:53.359
Look at the report.
Everyone was throwing punches.

05:53.393 --> 05:55.361
Including your client.

05:55.395 --> 05:56.596
Sitting this one out, Jared?

05:56.630 --> 05:58.397
Just the meetings
involving you.

05:58.432 --> 06:00.032
Look, he's got no record,

06:00.067 --> 06:01.901
and there's no way to tell
who started the fight.

06:01.935 --> 06:03.536
I'm reading.

06:04.972 --> 06:06.439
Stop biting your lip.

06:06.473 --> 06:08.241
Stop looking at me.

06:08.275 --> 06:09.709
She knows
that's a strong move.

06:09.743 --> 06:10.877
Oh, sometime today.

06:10.911 --> 06:12.579
Okay. Talk.

06:12.613 --> 06:13.913
All right.
The club manager

06:13.948 --> 06:15.248
has no interest
in pursuing this case.

06:15.282 --> 06:17.217
It's not my case.

06:17.251 --> 06:18.618
It's been assigned to
Ellen Swatello.

06:18.652 --> 06:19.786
No!
She <i>hates</i> us.

06:19.820 --> 06:21.220
She hates everybody.

06:21.255 --> 06:22.588
I'll talk to her,

06:22.623 --> 06:23.856
see if I can get her
to reduce the charges.

06:23.891 --> 06:25.458
Thank you.

06:27.928 --> 06:29.762
You're just being cruel.

06:31.865 --> 06:32.832
Stop.

06:32.866 --> 06:34.066
What?

06:34.101 --> 06:36.602
Okay. Let's begin.

06:36.636 --> 06:38.871
Even though this is
an arbitration

06:38.905 --> 06:41.406
and the evidentiary rules
are relaxed,

06:41.441 --> 06:43.174
the rule of law still applies.

06:43.209 --> 06:45.076
All right, all right.

06:45.110 --> 06:46.744
Can we just do this, please?

06:46.778 --> 06:48.245
Sure.
How about ladies first?

06:48.280 --> 06:50.914
My client, Maya Paxton,
is seeking a divorce

06:50.949 --> 06:52.115
for loss of consortium.

06:52.150 --> 06:54.718
Mr. Paxton lost interest
in his wife.

06:54.752 --> 06:57.020
They haven't had sex
in eight months,

06:57.054 --> 06:58.288
which suggests that he reverted
to his old ways.

06:58.322 --> 06:59.856
We're gonna show
that Rick Paxton

06:59.890 --> 07:01.457
violated the infidelity clause
in the prenup.

07:01.491 --> 07:03.092
That's not true.

07:03.894 --> 07:05.461
Interesting theory.

07:05.496 --> 07:07.263
I don't suppose
you have any proof?

07:07.297 --> 07:09.431
Aside from the fact he's obviously
grown tired of sleeping --

07:09.466 --> 07:11.000
Glenna!

07:11.034 --> 07:13.201
He's right. Unless
you want to get sanctioned,

07:13.236 --> 07:14.402
I wouldn't finish that sentence.

07:14.437 --> 07:15.837
We're working
on the proof.

07:15.872 --> 07:17.005
We'll find it.
Trust me.

07:17.039 --> 07:19.141
When someone cheats,
I find out eventually.

07:19.175 --> 07:21.510
Because of Mr. Paxton's
sexual history,

07:21.544 --> 07:24.046
dual infidelity clauses were instituted,
punishing both parties.

07:24.080 --> 07:25.848
I'm aware of that.

07:25.882 --> 07:27.817
Well, it's hard for my
client to have sex with his wife

07:27.852 --> 07:30.955
if she's always in Florida
doing her home-shopping show.

07:30.989 --> 07:32.690
I-it's even harder
to have sex

07:32.724 --> 07:34.558
when her husband's crossing
the Atlantic in a balloon.

07:34.593 --> 07:37.729
Assuming he didn't have
his girlfriend <i>in</i> the balloon.

07:37.763 --> 07:39.897
Whoa.
Whoa, now, hold on.

07:39.932 --> 07:42.800
Now, it's one thing to say
that I cheated on Maya,

07:42.835 --> 07:45.436
it's another to say that
I cheated on my solo flight.

07:45.470 --> 07:47.338
Wow, so glad to see

07:47.372 --> 07:49.039
you have your priorities
in order, Rick.

07:49.074 --> 07:51.475
I mean, God forbid you'd cheat
on a balloon.

07:57.314 --> 07:59.849
Your honor,
I believe the prosecution --

07:59.884 --> 08:02.152
who, by the way,
looks radiant today --

08:02.186 --> 08:04.988
has a motion to reduce
the charges?

08:05.023 --> 08:09.026
I'm aware Mr. Bash spoke
to my <i>happily</i> engaged colleague,

08:09.061 --> 08:10.528
Janie Ross.

08:10.562 --> 08:11.896
Ohh. She went
for your knees there, bro.

08:11.931 --> 08:13.898
Unsportsmanlike conduct,
your honor.

08:13.933 --> 08:15.500
It does seem a bit personal.

08:15.534 --> 08:17.502
No kidding.
Thank you. Your honor.

08:17.537 --> 08:19.237
But new evidence
has come to light

08:19.272 --> 08:20.605
that requires a new charge
be added --

08:20.640 --> 08:22.040
driving under the influence.

08:22.074 --> 08:24.642
D.U.I.?
Come on, this was a little...

08:24.676 --> 08:25.910
A donnybrook.

08:25.944 --> 08:27.711
Which your client
drove to drunk.

08:27.746 --> 08:29.013
We have security-camera footage

08:29.047 --> 08:30.514
of the defendant
driving recklessly

08:30.548 --> 08:32.515
across a golf course
and up to the strip club.

08:32.549 --> 08:34.484
I drove up in a golf cart.

08:34.518 --> 08:35.717
And when
the police arrived,

08:35.753 --> 08:37.053
they took everyone's
blood alcohol,

08:37.087 --> 08:38.520
and Mr. Dubois' was above
the legal limit.

08:38.554 --> 08:40.054
Did you charge everyone

08:40.090 --> 08:41.756
who drove to the club
with d.U.I.?

08:41.792 --> 08:43.559
Just the ones who punched
the arresting officer.

08:43.594 --> 08:46.129
He wasn't wearing a uniform.

08:46.163 --> 08:47.596
I didn't mean to punch him.

08:47.631 --> 08:48.864
I didn't mean to punch you.

08:48.899 --> 08:50.232
It would have been helpful

08:50.267 --> 08:52.067
if you mentioned that detail
to us, Double D.

08:52.102 --> 08:53.636
Assault charges gone.

08:53.670 --> 08:55.505
Drunk-driving charges added.

08:55.539 --> 08:59.209
Wow, I didn't see <i>that</i> coming.
Did you, Mr. Bash?

09:07.604 --> 09:08.899
What kind of stunt was that?

09:09.038 --> 09:11.206
Look who's whining
about stunts.

09:11.240 --> 09:12.607
See you guys at trial.

09:12.642 --> 09:14.643
What is her problem?

09:14.677 --> 09:17.279
What is your problem?!

09:17.313 --> 09:18.847
Oh. Ohh. Really?

09:18.881 --> 09:20.081
-You asked.
-I didn't ask anything.

09:20.116 --> 09:21.149
You asked the question.

09:21.183 --> 09:22.417
-Hi.
-Hi.

09:22.451 --> 09:24.052
I've been here eight years,

09:24.086 --> 09:25.420
and I still have to deal
with imbeciles like you two,

09:25.455 --> 09:26.788
while your sainted
suck-up Janie,

09:26.823 --> 09:28.523
who's been here
half as long as me,

09:28.557 --> 09:29.858
gets bumped up to Major Crimes.

09:29.892 --> 09:32.427
Yeah, okay.
Have a nice day.

09:33.832 --> 09:36.126
Why can't I find a woman
like that?

09:36.127 --> 09:37.595
What's going on?

09:37.596 --> 09:38.391
If the cop's so pissed,

09:38.393 --> 09:39.694
why don't they just stick
with the assault?

09:39.728 --> 09:41.329
'Cause if they just
charged you

09:41.363 --> 09:42.764
and not everyone
who threw a punch,

09:42.798 --> 09:43.964
we'd argue selective
prosecution.

09:43.999 --> 09:45.366
Now they can go after just you.

09:45.400 --> 09:46.900
Yeah, they're gonna ask
for jail time,

09:46.935 --> 09:48.702
and if you're convicted,
they'll get it.

09:48.736 --> 09:50.970
Guys, I had two beers.
I wasn't drunk.

09:51.005 --> 09:52.438
Again, where were you

09:52.473 --> 09:53.839
when you got the call
to go to the club?

09:53.874 --> 09:55.174
I was kicking it at home.

09:55.208 --> 09:56.508
Okay, when you say
"Kicking it" --

09:56.542 --> 09:58.777
feel free to join us
in this decade --

09:58.811 --> 10:00.145
where would that be?

10:01.747 --> 10:03.981
That's not a tough
question. Where were you?

10:04.016 --> 10:06.517
I live with my grandmother.

10:06.552 --> 10:09.587
I got in the game
just as the economy tanked,

10:09.621 --> 10:12.123
so I was the last hired
and the first fired.

10:12.158 --> 10:15.528
Couldn't keep the condo,
so I came here.

10:15.562 --> 10:18.264
Are you gonna be able
to pay us?

10:18.299 --> 10:21.936
I was kind of hoping
you had a pro bono policy.

10:21.970 --> 10:23.604
"Bro Bono."

10:23.639 --> 10:24.572
Hey, Nana.

10:24.607 --> 10:26.341
Hey, Danny, come on!

10:26.375 --> 10:28.076
We got to get to the market.

10:28.110 --> 10:30.311
We miss free samples
after 5:00.

10:30.346 --> 10:35.117
If I get a D.U.I.,
do I lose my license?

10:35.151 --> 10:37.319
Yeah, probably.
For a while.

10:37.353 --> 10:39.955
I drive my grandmother
and her friends

10:39.989 --> 10:41.223
to the doctor and errands.

10:41.257 --> 10:43.358
I thought it'd be
a pain in the ass,

10:43.393 --> 10:44.793
but turns out
they keep me young.

10:44.828 --> 10:45.928
Danny! Come on!

10:45.962 --> 10:46.996
All right, all right.

10:47.030 --> 10:49.565
For God's sake, come on.

10:51.034 --> 10:52.401
Admit it!

10:52.435 --> 10:54.203
You're happy that Danny's fallen
on rough times.

10:54.237 --> 10:56.038
He was a dick to you
in high school.

10:56.072 --> 10:57.706
That's not true, Peter,

10:57.741 --> 10:59.475
because there,
but for the grace of God, go I.

10:59.509 --> 11:00.943
