Your colleagues only succeeded

11:06.083 --> 11:07.617
in getting Rick
and his lawyer angry.

11:07.651 --> 11:09.585
And what a raging bitch.

11:09.620 --> 11:11.954
Well, Hanna and Karp know that
your husband's a public figure

11:11.989 --> 11:13.589
and he wants to keep
the divorce quiet.

11:13.624 --> 11:15.358
But the threat
of blowing up the arbitration

11:15.392 --> 11:17.794
and taking this to a public
trial is sound legal advice.

11:17.828 --> 11:19.663
It just lacks
human compassion

11:19.697 --> 11:21.998
and puts more money
into our firm and theirs.

11:23.333 --> 11:25.635
I appreciate the honesty.

11:25.669 --> 11:28.137
Could use a little bit of that
in my life.

11:28.172 --> 11:29.272
Thank you.

11:29.306 --> 11:30.907
Anytime!

11:30.942 --> 11:32.642
We're open three days a week.

11:32.676 --> 11:34.944
You really are determined
to get us fired, aren't you?

11:34.978 --> 11:36.346
<i>Carmen talked</i>
<i>to a stripper</i>

11:36.380 --> 11:37.747
<i>who saw Danny break up</i>
<i>the fight.</i>

11:37.782 --> 11:39.116
<i>Why not put her on the stand?</i>

11:39.150 --> 11:41.018
Thought about it,
but jurors don't like strippers.

11:41.052 --> 11:42.586
You know who
they do love? Old people.

11:42.621 --> 11:45.056
Gonna talk to Danny's
grandmother and her friends,

11:45.090 --> 11:47.025
see if any of them noticed that
Danny was sober when he left.

11:47.059 --> 11:48.593
<i>I love old people.</i>

11:48.628 --> 11:50.896
<i>I tried to live in</i>
<i>a retirement home once.</i>

11:50.930 --> 11:53.832
<i>They're clean, there's no</i>
<i>stigma to being housebound,</i>

11:53.867 --> 11:55.200
<i>and the food is delicious.</i>

11:55.235 --> 11:56.568
<i>Let me handle this.</i>

11:56.602 --> 11:58.370
You got it, pal.
Just keep your eye on the ball.

11:58.404 --> 12:01.106
I got a call
from Maya Paxton.

12:01.140 --> 12:03.810
She was very impressed
with your candor this afternoon.

12:03.844 --> 12:06.512
Me? Not so much.
Hi, Pindar.

12:06.547 --> 12:08.013
<i>Hello, sir.</i>

12:08.048 --> 12:09.014
You upset?

12:09.049 --> 12:10.549
Well, we're not

12:10.584 --> 12:11.884
the poverty law center, Jared.

12:11.918 --> 12:14.653
We're actually in this
to make a profit.

12:14.687 --> 12:16.855
However, Maya liked you so much,

12:16.889 --> 12:19.924
she wants you
on the Paxton arbitration.

12:19.958 --> 12:21.725
With Hanna?

12:21.760 --> 12:23.260
Well, I-I need him
on the assault case.

12:23.294 --> 12:24.995
Damien can fill you in
with the details.

12:25.029 --> 12:26.996
Or Hanna.
Probably Hanna.

12:27.031 --> 12:28.397
Yeah.

12:30.534 --> 12:33.369
Uh, is there something
I should know about those two?

12:33.403 --> 12:35.504
-No.
-Really?

12:35.539 --> 12:36.572
No.

12:36.606 --> 12:38.240
There's been some talk.

12:38.275 --> 12:42.110
I-I don't listen
to...that...kind of stuff.

12:42.145 --> 12:44.279
Really? Hmm.

12:44.313 --> 12:46.548
All right. Hmm.

12:51.922 --> 12:54.023
We all together?

12:58.962 --> 13:00.897
<i>I am, of course,</i>
<i>Pindar Singh.</i>

13:00.931 --> 13:02.598
<i>I wish I could be there</i>
<i>with you today,</i>

13:02.633 --> 13:04.133
<i>but I am unfortunately</i>
<i>stuck in London.</i>

13:04.168 --> 13:05.702
<i>That's bullshit.</i>

13:05.736 --> 13:07.838
-<i>Get out of here!</i>
-<i>Bullshit!</i>

13:09.107 --> 13:12.542
<i>I want to thank you</i>
<i>all for coming today.</i>

13:12.577 --> 13:14.778
Whatever we can do
to help my grandson.

13:14.812 --> 13:17.080
<i>Okay. You live at</i>
<i>the Palms. Stellar facility.</i>

13:17.114 --> 13:20.950
<i>Not as nice as Coldwater Creek,</i>
<i>but a much nicer piano.</i>

13:20.984 --> 13:23.619
I hate the parrot
in the lobby. Nasty bird.

13:23.653 --> 13:25.153
<i>I'm sorry.</i>
<i>Who said that?</i>

13:25.188 --> 13:27.522
-Me. I hate birds.
-<i>Me too.</i>

13:27.556 --> 13:29.657
<i>Did you know that birds</i>
<i>carry more germs than rodents?</i>

13:29.692 --> 13:31.860
I used to shoot 'em
out of my bedroom window

13:31.894 --> 13:34.896
till the home took away
my second amendment rights.

13:34.931 --> 13:36.932
<i>Perhaps we can kill</i>
<i>birds together someday, miss...</i>

13:36.966 --> 13:39.935
-Nanette.
-<i>...Nanette.</i>

13:39.969 --> 13:43.939
<i>Uh, how much did Danny</i>
<i>have to drink that night?</i>

13:43.973 --> 13:46.208
We were at my place
watching "Ice Road Truckers,"

13:46.242 --> 13:47.709
and Danny dropped by
after his run.

13:47.744 --> 13:49.911
We tend to congregate
in my room.

13:49.946 --> 13:51.213
Best TV in the village.

13:51.247 --> 13:54.617
<i>Nanette is talking!</i>

13:54.651 --> 13:56.819
<i>Thank you.</i>

13:56.854 --> 13:58.187
<i>Hi.</i>

13:58.222 --> 14:00.123
Hi.

14:00.157 --> 14:03.193
<i>Um, how much</i>
<i>did Danny have to drink?</i>

14:03.227 --> 14:04.894
He was on his second beer

14:04.929 --> 14:06.930
when the phone call came
from his friend.

14:06.964 --> 14:09.465
<i>Is there any way</i>
<i>to back up your recollection</i>

14:09.500 --> 14:11.234
<i>that Danny only had two beers?</i>

14:11.268 --> 14:13.970
Well, I still have
four beers from that six-pack

14:14.004 --> 14:15.405
in my fridge.

14:15.439 --> 14:16.739
Would that help?

14:16.773 --> 14:18.574
<i>Doesn't hurt...</i>

14:18.609 --> 14:20.009
<i>Nanette.</i>

14:20.044 --> 14:22.078
Pindar.

14:27.218 --> 14:28.986
The plans for my dream house

14:29.020 --> 14:30.821
were drawn up
before I even met Maya.

14:30.855 --> 14:33.290
I mean, if there's any dream
involved here, it's <i>mine.</i>

14:33.324 --> 14:34.658
Rick can have it.

14:34.692 --> 14:35.959
Ain't no thing.

14:35.994 --> 14:37.528
I don't want it.

14:37.562 --> 14:40.164
Maya,
we didn't agree to this.

14:40.198 --> 14:43.133
Jared and I discussed it
on the way over,

14:43.168 --> 14:44.835
and the house is a disaster.

14:44.870 --> 14:46.337
Well, fine.

14:46.371 --> 14:48.940
Uh, then Maya can have the --
the cabin in Aspen.

14:48.974 --> 14:50.508
I mean, she's the skier
in the family --

14:50.542 --> 14:52.710
or <i>was</i> the skier.

14:52.745 --> 14:54.012
Mm.

14:54.046 --> 14:55.414
How did you let this happen?

14:55.448 --> 14:56.982
-Me?
-Yeah, you.

14:57.017 --> 14:58.784
Let's keep moving.
We can be done in an hour.

14:58.818 --> 15:00.753
Great.
I'll make a tee time for 2:00.

15:00.787 --> 15:02.021
Hey, wait a minute!

15:02.056 --> 15:03.623
Yes. Everybody just needs
to stop being so...

15:03.657 --> 15:04.857
Decent?

15:04.892 --> 15:06.459
This is a complicated case.

15:06.494 --> 15:08.862
There are
irreconcilable differences.

15:08.896 --> 15:10.864
Like the fact that Mr. Paxton

15:10.898 --> 15:12.198
is cheating on his wife.

15:12.233 --> 15:13.466
Oh, absent proof.

15:13.501 --> 15:14.967
I don't see how you think...

15:17.437 --> 15:19.070
We got phone records, e-mails,

15:19.105 --> 15:22.006
and...those pictures
are pretty clear evidence

15:22.041 --> 15:23.208
of a relationship.

15:27.613 --> 15:29.581
Your client's
little transgression

15:29.615 --> 15:30.749
just triggered item five...

15:30.783 --> 15:32.751
to the tune of $60 million.

15:32.785 --> 15:34.853
Fine.

15:34.887 --> 15:36.755
I raise you...

15:36.789 --> 15:39.624
another $60 million.

15:39.659 --> 15:41.359
Whoa.

15:43.362 --> 15:46.364
Wait a minute.

15:46.398 --> 15:50.668
Both sleeping
with the same mistress?

15:51.870 --> 15:53.704
How very green of you.

15:56.341 --> 15:57.474
Put them together, it's funner.

15:57.509 --> 15:59.009
-Wow.
-Yeah.

16:00.298 --> 16:01.377
Why didn't you tell us?

16:01.378 --> 16:02.679
It's not what it looks like.

16:02.800 --> 16:04.639
Question for the scary lady.

16:06.991 --> 16:08.292
<i>That</i> one.

16:08.326 --> 16:09.693
Why are we seeing this crap now?

16:09.727 --> 16:11.327
Why are we just seeing yours?

16:11.362 --> 16:12.863
We just learned about it.

16:12.897 --> 16:14.097
Oh, please.

16:14.131 --> 16:16.399
And if you hadn't spent
so much time

16:16.434 --> 16:18.068
trolling the sludge
to get your client

16:18.102 --> 16:20.003
a payoff she doesn't deserve,
we wouldn't have been forced

16:20.037 --> 16:21.805
to counter your
unsubstantiated story with ours.

16:21.839 --> 16:23.106
It's a draw, people.

16:23.140 --> 16:24.307
Let's go home.

16:24.342 --> 16:26.776
It was a kiss goodbye.

16:26.811 --> 16:28.144
I didn't cheat.

16:28.179 --> 16:29.579
I know.

16:29.614 --> 16:31.281
We're the last of
a dying breed, Maya.

16:31.315 --> 16:33.450
You dumped me.
Why am <i>i</i> the one who cheated?

16:33.484 --> 16:34.985
Okay. Hanna and I
didn't have sex.

16:35.019 --> 16:36.119
Let's put that to bed.

16:36.154 --> 16:38.388
Okay, since both clients

16:38.422 --> 16:39.889
violated the infidelity clause,

16:39.924 --> 16:41.658
your client isn't entitled
to $60 million.

16:41.692 --> 16:42.626
Well, fine.

16:42.660 --> 16:45.028
M-maybe I did cheat.

16:45.062 --> 16:47.296
But that doesn't mean
I don't love you.

16:48.999 --> 16:50.867
Maya.

16:50.901 --> 16:53.270
That sounded an awful lot
like an admission of an affair.

16:53.305 --> 16:55.539
-Uh, he said "maybe."
-What were you thinking?

16:55.574 --> 16:57.241
-I can't believe you.
-Carmen?

16:57.276 --> 16:59.344
You want me to find out
who's cheating on who.

16:59.378 --> 17:00.778
Okay, you couldn't
possibly have known

17:00.813 --> 17:01.880
I was gonna ask you that.

17:01.914 --> 17:03.581
I'll take care of it.

17:09.589 --> 17:10.857
Where'd everybody go?

17:10.891 --> 17:13.226
<i>You'll be great.</i>
<i>Don't be nervous.</i>

17:13.260 --> 17:15.161
I'll be fine!

17:15.195 --> 17:16.863
You've walked me
through my testimony

17:16.896 --> 17:18.198
seven times.

17:18.232 --> 17:20.465
<i>Leave me on for the trial.</i>

17:23.170 --> 17:25.271
Did you bring the remaining
four beers from the six-pack?

17:25.306 --> 17:26.640
They're right there
next to you.

17:26.674 --> 17:28.709
Oh.

17:28.743 --> 17:30.310
Your honor, I'd ask
that these beers be marked

17:30.344 --> 17:32.011
-as defense exhibit "C."
-So marked.

17:32.046 --> 17:33.746
How do you know these are
the same beers, ma'am?

17:33.781 --> 17:35.314
I don't drink,

17:35.349 --> 17:36.916
but I always keep a six-pack
in the fridge for Danny.

17:36.950 --> 17:39.585
Oh, so sweet.

17:39.619 --> 17:41.019
Now, I assume the prosecution

17:41.054 --> 17:44.689
will attack your memory
based on...

17:44.723 --> 17:45.856
My age.

17:45.891 --> 17:46.991
You can say it.

17:47.025 --> 17:48.859
I'm 74.

17:51.762 --> 17:53.630
"The Moon is Blue."

17:53.664 --> 17:56.467
William Holden
and David Niven.

17:56.501 --> 17:59.870
Written by F. Hugh Herbert,
directed by Otto Preminger,

17:59.904 --> 18:01.705
in 1953.

18:01.740 --> 18:04.108
Nanette has memorized
every movie

18:04.142 --> 18:05.276
for the past 60 years.

18:05.310 --> 18:07.445
Miss Swatello...

18:07.479 --> 18:08.613
care to challenge her memory?

18:08.647 --> 18:10.148
Your honor?

18:10.182 --> 18:12.284
Uh, "Leprechaun"?

18:12.318 --> 18:14.420
Nice.

18:14.454 --> 18:17.122
Written and directed
by Mark Jones in 1993,

18:17.157 --> 18:19.158
starring Warwick Davis

18:19.192 --> 18:21.794
and...a young Jennifer Aniston.

18:21.829 --> 18:23.730
Yeah.

18:23.764 --> 18:25.032
It's a parlor trick.

18:25.066 --> 18:26.567
It doesn't show her ability

18:26.601 --> 18:28.903
to remember relevant details
in a given moment.

18:28.937 --> 18:30.504
Which is why I brought this!

18:30.539 --> 18:32.173
Your honor,
with the court's permission,

18:32.207 --> 18:34.441
I'd like to blindfold Nanette
to prove her recall.

18:34.475 --> 18:36.076
Granted.

18:46.186 --> 18:47.787
Nanette...

18:47.821 --> 18:50.723
The juror in the back row,
second from the right,

18:50.757 --> 18:52.190
what's she wearing?

18:52.225 --> 18:54.860
Tangerine top,
almost matches her hair.

18:56.730 --> 18:59.198
How about the D.A.,
Miss Swatello?

18:59.232 --> 19:01.600
Gray pants, gray jacket,

19:01.634 --> 19:04.169
even her shoes --
everything is gray.

19:04.203 --> 19:06.472
The mural
behind me -- what is it?

19:06.506 --> 19:08.674
Native Americans
greeting settlers

19:08.708 --> 19:10.042
at the Pacific Ocean.

19:10.076 --> 19:11.977
And what are they holding?

19:12.011 --> 19:13.245
Corn.

19:15.014 --> 19:18.249
Corn.

19:27.425 --> 19:28.992
Excuse me.

19:29.027 --> 19:30.961
-Hi.
- Can I help you?

19:30.995 --> 19:32.696
I've got a house
I want to build.

19:32.730 --> 19:34.298
I hear you're good
at drawing them.

19:34.332 --> 19:36.434
I'd love to help you, but...

19:41.574 --> 19:44.176
A kiss goodbye
while waiting for my car.

19:44.211 --> 19:46.980
Frozen, it looks like
something else.

19:47.014 --> 19:49.316
Yeah.
Frozen -- well...It looks hot.

19:49.350 --> 19:52.086
Maya and I met on the plans

19:52.120 --> 19:53.988
when Rick was out of town.

19:54.022 --> 19:55.789
Seriously, it was nothing.

19:55.823 --> 19:58.959
And was this nothing, too?

20:04.899 --> 20:08.235
Look,
I never slept with Rick.

20:08.269 --> 20:09.570
One time, we almost --

20:09.604 --> 20:11.639
You know, I could
subpoena you to tell us.

20:11.673 --> 20:15.310
And I could sit there
and keep my mouth shut.

20:16.646 --> 20:19.181
Or I could make stuff up about
Maya that you wouldn't like.

20:21.518 --> 20:24.654
Your memory is impressive,

20:24.688 --> 20:26.389
but I'd like to challenge you
one more time.

20:26.424 --> 20:29.893
Do you remember where you were
the night of May 6, 1998?

20:29.928 --> 20:31.495
Objection.

20:31.530 --> 20:33.197
What does that have to do
with the events on August 2nd?

20:33.231 --> 20:34.965
It's the date
Nanette Norton

20:34.999 --> 20:36.400
was convicted of prostitution.

20:38.669 --> 20:40.503
Miss Norton
has never been --

20:40.537 --> 20:41.904
Miss Norton wasn't.

20:41.939 --> 20:43.640
But Nancy Blesoe was.

20:43.674 --> 20:46.509
Or was it Miranda Cain?

20:46.543 --> 20:49.011
You've had several aliases,
haven't you?

20:52.715 --> 20:53.782
Yes.

20:53.816 --> 20:55.084
<i>Oh, my God!</i>

20:55.118 --> 20:57.152
<i>My Nanette's a whore!</i>

20:58.287 --> 20:59.788
But I'm not lying about Danny!

20:59.823 --> 21:01.924
He only drank <i>two</i> beers.

21:01.958 --> 21:03.426
Due respect,

21:03.460 --> 21:05.161
but everything about you
is a lie.

21:05.195 --> 21:07.396
You've been convicted
of credit-card fraud,

21:07.431 --> 21:10.399
kiting checks, and three other
prostitution convictions.

21:10.433 --> 21:11.934
In fact,

21:11.968 --> 21:13.535
I'm starting to think
maybe today's not the first time

21:13.570 --> 21:15.237
you were asked to be
blindfolded.

21:15.271 --> 21:18.073
Was it?

21:20.377 --> 21:22.411
So, Allison was in love
with Rick Paxton,

21:22.446 --> 21:23.813
but not Maya?

21:23.848 --> 21:24.947
Well, that's one
for the home team.

21:24.982 --> 21:26.182
Well, not so fast.

21:26.216 --> 21:27.516
Maya <i>was</i> in love
with Rick Paxton,

21:27.551 --> 21:29.185
but Paxton wasn't in love
with her.

21:29.220 --> 21:30.787
In fact,
they never even had sex.

21:30.821 --> 21:32.022
Well, they almost did
but didn't.

21:32.056 --> 21:33.357
She didn't say why.

21:33.391 --> 21:35.159
Wait --
when Maya confronted Rick

21:35.193 --> 21:36.894
about having the affair
with Allison,

21:36.929 --> 21:38.329
he basically admitted to it,

21:38.363 --> 21:40.231
and now she's saying
that they didn't consummate?

21:40.265 --> 21:41.366
Why would Allison be lying?

21:41.400 --> 21:42.534
Maybe she's not.

21:42.568 --> 21:44.102
Do you think <i>he</i> is?

21:44.137 --> 21:45.737
Paxton
is admitting to an affair

21:45.772 --> 21:47.673
-so he can lose $11 million.
-He's a guy.

21:47.707 --> 21:50.510
Guy's accused of cheating --
his first instinct is to lie.

21:50.544 --> 21:52.545
Rick's first instinct
is to admit it?

21:52.579 --> 21:54.647
Well,
maybe he <i>was</i> being honest

21:54.681 --> 21:57.282
about what really happened
when they were together,

21:57.317 --> 21:58.817
instead of...lying about it.

21:58.851 --> 22:00.685
He's hiding something.

22:00.720 --> 22:02.954
You getting a blip
on the gaydar?

22:02.988 --> 22:05.923
The guy's a notorious
international womanizer.

22:05.957 --> 22:07.658
Hell, he markets himself
that way.

22:07.692 --> 22:09.359
Then...What?

22:09.393 --> 22:10.493
What do men lie about?

22:10.528 --> 22:12.028
-Money.
-Size.

22:12.062 --> 22:13.630
-<i>Everything.</i>
-Girth.

22:13.664 --> 22:15.366
Okay.
A little angry. All right?

22:15.400 --> 22:16.667
You're in the right ballpark.

22:16.701 --> 22:17.868
As Rick Paxton will tell you,

22:17.902 --> 22:19.369
it's not the size
of the balloon,

22:19.404 --> 22:21.138
it's whether you can get it
off the ground.

22:21.172 --> 22:22.406
Spare us the analogies.

22:22.440 --> 22:24.141
He couldn't get an erection.

22:24.175 --> 22:25.943
Okay,
so if he was willing

22:25.977 --> 22:28.045
to pay off the prenup to keep
his private business private,

22:28.079 --> 22:30.213
then how are we gonna get him
to admit to it?

22:34.051 --> 22:36.553
This is why you hire us.

22:48.466 --> 22:51.802
My sweet old lady
turned out to be a hooker.

22:51.836 --> 22:54.572
Who doesn't have one
of those in their lives?

22:54.606 --> 22:56.474
Makes me
want to play a song.

22:56.508 --> 22:57.942
That's unfortunate.

22:57.976 --> 22:59.276
All right.
You name the artist.

22:59.311 --> 23:01.078
Okay. Cold War Kids.

23:01.113 --> 23:02.480
Ah, something between
the Eagles or AC/DC.

23:02.514 --> 23:03.681
But you choose --
just as long as it's...

23:03.715 --> 23:04.949
The Eagles or AC/DC.

23:04.983 --> 23:06.216
That -- no --
I don't think so.

23:06.251 --> 23:08.185
Hey.
I need to talk to you.

23:08.220 --> 23:09.353
No, me first.

23:09.388 --> 23:10.988
Nanette imploded
on the stand today.

23:11.023 --> 23:12.824
So we're stuck with the rising
blood alcohol defense.

23:12.858 --> 23:15.059
Well, maybe the relevant
time isn't when he drank

23:15.094 --> 23:16.428
but whether the alcohol
was in his system

23:16.462 --> 23:18.030
when he got in the golf cart.

23:18.064 --> 23:19.932
Yeah, I like it,
but the jury needs something

23:19.966 --> 23:22.001
they can sink their teeth into,
not an anatomy lesson.

23:22.035 --> 23:23.303
Speaking of anatomy,

23:23.337 --> 23:24.771
